"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-how-to-watch-the-2024-olympic-games-opening-ceremony\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Below is everything you need to know about how to watch the 2024 Olympic Opening Ceremony in Paris, France which will take place Friday, July 25.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 93, \"end\": 98, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998834509892, \"rank\": 1.1654920756034693e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 100, \"end\": 106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9974258369670697, \"rank\": 0.0018730385958637182, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ceremonies have been important to the Olympic Games for much of its history, with the Opening Ceremony serving as a signpost of the commencement of the games.\", \"from\": 147, \"to\": 305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 233, \"end\": 249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.99983032589978, \"rank\": 0.0001673122579560208, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games_ceremony\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The key symbol at this ceremony is the Olympic cauldron being lit by the Olympic torch at the end of the torch's relay journey.\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 433, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame is initially lit in Olympia, Greece.\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympia, Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Olympia, Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia,_Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From there, it travels to the host city.\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 522, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the event is ceremonially important, a few events have already taken place in the few days before Friday, which is customary.\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This year's ceremony in Paris is the first to ever take place outside of a stadium.\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 681, \"end\": 686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998834509892, \"rank\": 1.1654920756034693e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris developed a bold plan for the torch-lighting this year, featuring a boat parade down the Seine, with each country getting its own boat.\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 741, \"end\": 746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998834509892, \"rank\": 1.1654920756034693e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 836, \"end\": 841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999785409275, \"rank\": 2.0893198953584812e-08, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The parade features 10,500 athletes across a route of about 3.7 miles and more expanded spectating options for fans in Paris.\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 1008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1002, \"end\": 1007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998834509892, \"rank\": 1.1654920756034693e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Opening Ceremony for Paris 2024 will take place on Friday, July 26 with the parade starting at 7:30 p.m. Paris time.\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1119, \"end\": 1124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998834509892, \"rank\": 1.1654920756034693e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In America, that puts it at 1:30 p.m.\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1168, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ET 12:30 p.m. CT, and 10:30 a.m. PT.\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1205, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1202, \"end\": 1204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_Time_Zone\", \"score\": 0.9999999872211448, \"rank\": 1.2658049747159075e-08, \"text\": \"PT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_Time_Zone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pacific_Time_Zone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year's broadcast should be exciting, with each of the country's boats outfitted with cameras to give fans near and far a close look at all of the Olympic athletes as they travel down the river.\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1405, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In America, you can watch the ceremony on NBC.\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1449, \"end\": 1452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9545905156633923, \"rank\": 0.0475695181828034, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you are looking for a streaming option, you can watch on Peacock or Fubo.tv.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can also watch on NBC's website for the Olympics,nbcolympics.com.\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1556, \"end\": 1559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9545905156633923, \"rank\": 0.0475695181828034, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mike Tirico will host, accompanied by Kelly Clarkson and Peyton Manning.\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1677, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1605, \"end\": 1616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mike Tirico\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Tirico\"}, {\"begin\": 1643, \"end\": 1657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelly Clarkson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Clarkson\"}, {\"begin\": 1662, \"end\": 1676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peyton_Manning\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Peyton Manning\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peyton_Manning\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peyton_Manning\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized conten